      "id": 6341,
      "name": "Mariusz",
      "username": "mowczar",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/47e85d/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2022-04-05T06:57:34.789Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I didn\u2019t mean music, I meant a beep that would allow each leg to rhythmically press the pedals (kind of like a metronome), the frequency of which for each leg would be consistent with the cadence set in the training task and/or set by the exerciser himself. In EGR mode, this is easy as the current preset power in the training program at a constant cadence is kept fairly constant by the trainer.<br>\nThis additional mode will also allow you to train on equal work and maintaining a constant cadence for both legs, which I have a slight problem with.</p>",
